io.lambdacube.aspecio.aspect.interceptor.arguments

Interface Arguments

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ArgumentsTrait

    public interface Arguments
extends ArgumentsTrait

    This class represents the arguments passed to an intercepted method. When requested to, Aspecio will create an instance for each invocation, and possibly allow an Advice to change them before an invocation.

    Arguments generated by Aspecio do not box primitive types, and as such boxed and non-boxed types have to be managed separately.

    Arguments generated by Aspecio are immutable and thus thread-safe. They implement Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() and thus can be used as keys for cache.
